{"id":31,"date":"2025-03-27T11:02:16","date_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:02:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/?p=31"},"modified":"2025-03-27T11:02:26","modified_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:02:26","slug":"classic-beef-stroganoff","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/2025\/03\/27\/classic-beef-stroganoff\/","title":{"rendered":"Classic Beef Stroganoff"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>A rich and creamy Russian dish with tender beef, mushrooms, and a savory sauce served over egg noodles or rice.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Ingredients:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>500g beef sirloin, thinly sliced<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp olive oil<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp butter<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 onion, finely chopped<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>3 cloves garlic, minced<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>200g mushrooms, sliced<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp flour<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 cup beef broth<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 cup sour cream<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tsp Dijon mustard<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp Worcestershire sauce<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Salt and pepper to taste<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1\/2 tsp smoked paprika<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cooked egg noodles or rice<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Instructions:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Prepare the Beef:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Slice the beef thinly against the grain for tenderness.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Season with salt, pepper, and smoked paprika.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cook the Beef:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add the beef and sear for 2 minutes per side. Remove and set aside.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saut\u00e9 the Vegetables:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In the same pan, add butter and let it melt.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Saut\u00e9 onions until soft, then add garlic and mushrooms. Cook until mushrooms are golden brown.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Make the Sauce:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sprinkle flour over the mushroom mixture and stir for 1 minute.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Slowly add beef broth while stirring to avoid lumps.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mix in Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, and sour cream. Stir well.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Combine:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Return the beef to the pan and simmer for 5 minutes until the sauce thickens.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Serve:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Serve over egg noodles or rice, garnished with fresh parsley.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Tips:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Use high-quality beef for the best texture.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Adjust the thickness of the sauce with more broth if needed.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A rich and creamy Russian dish with tender beef, mushrooms, and a savory sauce served over egg noodles or rice. Ingredients: Instructions: Tips:<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":32,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[3],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-31","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-main-courses"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/w